2. Empirical and Methodological Syntheses in Bioethics
Systematic reviews reveal:
Empirical bioethics: Growing integration of social science data (surveys, qualitative studies) with normative analysis. A 2020 meta-review found systematic reviews of empirical literature on topics like ethics committees, informed consent, and end-of-life decisions, but noted variability in quality and methods. 

