Systematic reviews of HTI ethical frameworks reveal dozens of models, often clustering around motivations (e.g., risk mitigation), objectives (guiding design/implementation), and methods (deliberative, multicriteria). Many rely on an "ethics of caution" rather than deeper questioning of technological paradigms. 

